If I read it correctly, this is how a file token is generated, which is supposed to be secure:<p><pre><code>     file.id = md5(file.name + (Math.random() * 1000));
</code></pre>
First of all please do not use MD5 for anything anymore, it has known collisions. But you shouldn&#x27;t also use any hash functions here at all: just generate a long enough random token. Math.random is not a secure PRNG, use crypto.randomBytes in Node or window.crypto.getRandomValues in browsers.<p>PS And multiplication by 1000... is it just for fun?
